Class MatrixFormulationConcrete

  • java.lang.Object

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class MatrixFormulationConcrete
extends MatrixFormulationAbstract
implements java.io.Serializable
    The MatrixFormulationConcrete class provides the specific methods for evaluating a system dynamics model. MatrixFormulationConcrete instances are written and compiled dynamically at engine run time. This instance is an example that is used to demonstrate and test the functions of this automatically generated class.
